The generic DwarfSpec live self-test set is therefore the current export,
framework-hardening, interaction, and scheduler/cleanup specs plus the cover,
failing, interaction, and runner-probe fixtures. The DwarfUI consumer set is
the two tooltip specs plus the tooltip screen and tooltip overlay fixtures.

#### Phase 0 import and runtime dependency inventory

| Dependency or seam | Current users | Extraction disposition |
|---|---|---|
| `busted.core`, `busted`, `busted.modules.filter_loader`, `busted.modules.test_file_loader`, `busted.execute` | `busted_host.lua` | DwarfSpec runtime dependency and in-process host. |
| `busted.outputHandlers.base` | `output_handler.lua` | DwarfSpec reporting adapter. |
| `luassert`, Penlight, Say, Mediator, Lua CLI Args, Lua Term | Transitive Busted source dependencies | Installed transitively by the DwarfSpec rock; only Lua-compatible source is exposed inside DFHack. |
| `system`, `lfs` | Busted/Penlight seams | DwarfSpec supplies the proven DFHack-native adapters instead of loading Lua 5.4 DLLs into Lua 5.3. |
| `json` | `busted_host.lua` | DFHack-native `require('json').encode`; retain inside the live host. |
| `gui`, `gui.widgets` | Generic and product fixtures plus `ds` input operations | DFHack runtime API; retain as live-only imports. |
| `plugins.overlay` | Overlay staging/product coverage | DFHack runtime API; generic staging moves to DwarfSpec while tooltip behavior remains in DwarfUI. |
| `dwarfui/tooltip`, `dwarfui/tooltip_registration` | Tooltip screen fixture, tooltip overlay fixture, and two tooltip specs | DwarfUI consumer-only imports; never move into DwarfSpec. |
| `Tools/Common.ps1` `Import-EnvironmentFile()` and `Resolve-DFHackRunner()` | PowerShell runner | The file remains DwarfUI-owned. The cross-platform CLI independently implements the documented configuration and runner-resolution contract. |
| Repository-relative `loadfile()` calls | Unit tests, entry points, host, `dy`, hardening spec | Replace moved code with installed `dwarfspec.*` modules and pass the consumer project root explicitly. |

There is no current DwarfUI callback injected into the generic `dy` object.
Tooltip specs import DwarfUI modules directly. The future
`Tests/dwarfspec/*.lua` custom-command contract is therefore a new consumer
extension seam, not a migration of an existing hidden callback.

#### Phase 0 options, environment, paths, and identifiers

Current external runner parameters are `Filter`, `FilterOut`, `Name`, `Tag`,
`ExcludeTag`, `Repeat`, `Spec`, `TimeoutSeconds`,
`PollIntervalMilliseconds`, `StartupDelayFrames`,
`LeaseTimeoutMilliseconds`, `LeaseCheckFrames`, `RunId`, `OverlayFixture`,
`DFHackRunner`, `DwarfFortressRoot`, and `EnvFile`. The bootstrap accepts
`filter`, `filter-out`, `name`, `tag`, `exclude-tag`, `repeat`, `seed`,
`defer-frames`, `lease-timeout-ms`, `lease-check-frames`, and `spec`; the current
PowerShell runner always uses the bootstrap's default seed of `1`.

| Current implicit contract | Current value | Required standalone input or owner |
|---|---|---|
| Repository root | Derived from `Tests/Automation/bootstrap.lua`'s source path | CLI resolves the consumer project root; installed modules resolve their own rock location independently. |
| Live spec root/suffix | `Tests/Automation/specs/**/*_live_spec.lua` | Consumer convention `Tests/**/*_spec.ds.lua`. |
| Screen fixture root | `Tests/Automation/fixtures/<name>.lua` | Explicit import; recommended `Tests/**/fixtures/*.fixture.lua`, with no mandatory root. |
| Overlay fixture root | `Tests/Automation/overlay_fixtures/<name>.lua` | Explicit importable fixture definition owned by the consumer or DwarfSpec self-tests. |
| Host/support paths | `Tests/Automation/{bootstrap,status,abort,support}/...` | Installed `dwarfspec.*` modules and CLI-owned entry points. |
| Busted source root | `.luarocks/share/lua/5.4` | Resolve the DwarfSpec rock's LuaRocks dependencies; do not assume a project-local tree or hardcoded Lua directory. |
| Native dependency root | `.luarocks/lib/lua/5.4` for local tests | External unit tooling only; never prepend this native directory inside DFHack Lua 5.3. |
| Runner configuration file | `.env.local`, defaulted by `EnvFile` | Optional project configuration under `Tests/dwarfspec/*.lua`, CLI options, and documented environment variables. |
| Runner executable | `MOD_COMMAND_RUNNER`, parameter, `GAME_ROOT/hack/dfhack-run.exe`, or `PATH` | `DFHACK_RUNNER`, `DFHACK_ROOT/hack/dfhack-run`, or `PATH`; legacy names may be accepted only through an explicit migration policy. |
| Game/DFHack root | `GAME_ROOT` | Explicit CLI/config/environment input for temporary overlay staging; do not infer it from the consumer repository. |
| Staged overlay directory | `<GAME_ROOT>/hack/scripts/gui` | Explicit validated DFHack installation path; stage only a unique run-owned file. |
| Staged overlay filename | `dwarfui_automation_<run-id>_<fixture>.lua` | DwarfSpec-owned `dwarfspec_<run-id>_<fixture>.lua` name with exact-path deletion. |
| Run identifier | `dwarfui-<32 hex characters>` | DwarfSpec-owned run id. |
| In-process ownership | `dfhack.dwarfui.automation` | `dfhack.dwarfspec`. |
| Human report prefix | `DWARFUI_AUTOMATION` | `DWARFSPEC`. |
| JSON report prefix | `DWARFUI_AUTOMATION_JSON` | `DWARFSPEC_JSON`. |
| Overlay rescan marker | `DWARFUI_OVERLAY_RESCAN_OK` | DwarfSpec-owned marker. |
| Optional result path | `.test-results/live/` appears only in the old plan; the current runner writes no coordination or report files | `.test-results/dwarfspec/` for optional artifacts only. |
| Package globals | Host prepends `package.path`, sets `package.preload.system/lfs`, `package.loaded.system/lfs`, and clears `package.loaded.busted` | DwarfSpec owns a documented, repeat-safe dependency bootstrap and must restore or deliberately retain each process-wide change under an explicit lifecycle contract. |
| Temporary live resources | Test screens, pointer-function patch, native mouse position, DFHack timeouts, overlay enable/focus changes, cleanup entries, and active-run lease | DwarfSpec run-scoped cleanup; product-specific tooltip registration restoration remains in DwarfUI specs/fixtures. |

#### Phase 0 reproducible baseline

Local toolchain and dependency versions:

- Lua `5.4.6` from the registered per-user Lua installation;
- LuaRocks `3.9.2`;
- Busted `2.3.0-1`;
- Luassert `1.9.0-1`;
- Penlight `1.15.0-1`;
- LuaSystem `0.3.0-2`; and
- LuaFileSystem `1.9.0-1`.

The shell did not initially contain the registered Lua installation on
`PATH`; the unmodified runner therefore stopped with `LuaRocks was not found on
PATH`. Prepending the registered Lua `bin` directory for that process and
running `Tools/Run-UnitTests.ps1` produced:

```text
93 successes / 0 failures / 0 errors / 0 pending
```

Live target versions reported through the configured `dfhack-run` executable:

- DFHack `53.15-r1`;
- Dwarf Fortress `v0.53.15 win64 STEAM`;
- embedded `Lua 5.3`; and
- `dfhack.is_core_context == true`.

`Tools/Run-AutomationTests.ps1` ran the default live suite as protocol 1,
generation 1, and produced:

```text
14 successes / 0 failures / 0 errors / 0 pending
state=passed cleanup_confirmed=true
```

The separate installed-overlay command
`Tools/Run-AutomationTests.ps1 -Spec tooltip_overlay_live_spec.lua
-OverlayFixture tooltip_probe` ran as generation 2 and produced:

```text
1 success / 0 failures / 0 errors / 0 pending
state=passed cleanup_confirmed=true
```

The runner reported successful rescans before and after the overlay run. A
direct post-run audit found zero `dwarfui_automation_*.lua` files in the live
DFHack GUI script directory.

